The paper discusses the use of context information to forecast the evolution of network conditions and optimize network performance, which falls under the category of networked systems and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for prediction and optimization, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the study of patterns and periodicity in human behavior and network dynamics, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of network performance, which could fall under the category of optimization and control (cs.SI).
